		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">Oasis Crowded? Go Overthere!<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Tue, Sep 12th 1:55 PM2000 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=5&mid=96878135914978&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=5&mid=96878135914978&num=0&post=1&replyto=96878135914978"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=96878135914978></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=362"><span id=Scholar>TyldakTallonZ</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br>19 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.50]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=TyldakTallonZ&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>At level 19 I decided that I'd had enough of the Oasis. On my server, TZ, it's a really crowded area of mostly level 10-20's. Plus the Oasis is a favorite PvP raiding area, since light players level 20-30 know they can 'hunt' darkies there and not get much in the way of opposition ( most of the 20+ darkies have moved on to better areas ). I finally packed my bags and headed for The Overthere. <br><br>I caught the barge at the dock in Oasis. This took me to Timorous Deep. I disembarked when the barge stopped and turned about 45 degrees to the right and walked straight. This brought me to a camp of Ogres where there was a dock. I noticed a fellow DE SK pounding on one of the ogres. I asked him about faction concerns and he assured me there was no faction loss in Oggok*. To be on the safe side, I declined to join in, and I fished until the big boat came. <br><br>I got on the boat and the other SK told me to stand in the middle of the boat, just behind the mast. He told me not to sit until the boat was well underway ( island not visible ) and to stay behind the mast. Apparently there's a bug that bumps you off the boat. I didn't check to see if he was right, I just did as I was advised.<br><br>We eventually disembarked at a pier in The Overthere. Assuming you don't attack anything, and you're an evil race, nothing there will bother you, but everyone con'ed apprehensive to me. I found the bank and the merchants. It's all pretty self-contained. I pretty readily got a bind at the bank. <br><br>I then headed out the East exit from the outpost, facing towards Warslick Woods. This is an important distinction - when under level 25 don't go messing around with the area just to the North.<br><br>I conjured up a pet and found I could pull blue con's and reverse kite them ( see Fear Kiting, Beginners Guide thread on this board ). I don't have great gear, and the mobs are a little more magic resistant than croc's in Oasis, so it was slow going at first. Be aware that nothing is KOS on you except the sarnaks. You'll start r-kiting a tiger, and it takes half your health and you think you're doing ok, but then a flunkie jumps you and you're at half health with no mana left. Oops. I stayed close to the gate and just got familiar with the local game.<br><br>After about 1/2 a level I found a group and was brought to the "mud hole". We got there by exiting the outpost, turning 45 degrees left, and going to the beach. We then stayed on the beach, continuing straight/west until we saw hills stretching out to the south. We then turned right/north and found the mud hole. There I noticed there were other groups gathered as well. While this area was slightly more dangerous for sarnack walk-by's, the game spawn was much more frequent.<br><br>Good points: I'm now up to 21 and so far, so good. There's been plenty of game, lots of peace and quiet, and no kill stealing. The only PvP disruptions I've noticed are level 30+'s who tangle with the occasional gnome or some such. <br><br>Bad points: Groups below level 25 can be hard to find sometimes. Be prepared to solo about half of the time. There's no place to train there. Getting new spells and skills inevitably means going home to Neriak. Stuff is expensive there! Once I got level 20 I needed to go back to Neriak to train in Double Attack. While I was there I bought many stacks of food, water, and bandages and put them in backpacks in the bank. I tried getting bones from newbies but had little luck. I have heard, however, that in Kunark's Field of Bone there are plenty of Iskar newbies with tons of bones to sell since skeletons are all over the place.<br><br>* - Just last night I ran into a DE necromancer at the bank who asked if I could buy her food and water from the local merchants. She said they would not sell to her. I asked why and she said, "Because I killed too many ogres in Timorous Deep." Hunter beware.<br><br>Hope this information proves useful. Please add to anything I missed!<br><br>Tyldak <br>Shadow Knight<br>Master Smith<br>Tallon Zek<br><a href="http://www.geocities.com/tyldaktallonz/" target=_new>http://www.geocities.com/tyldaktallonz/</a></p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=5><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=5&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" width=17 height=11> New Subject</a> | <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=5&mid=96878135914978&num=0&post=1&mid=96878135914978><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply" width=17 height=11> Reply to Thread</a></span></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="mform"><tr><td id="fs8">0 Posts [ <a href="/fsearch.html?base=class5">Search Forums</a> ]</nobr></td></tr></table>&nbsp;</td></tr>
